{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all schools to offer regular counselling to students",
        "additional_details": "Some children will not ask for help unless given a chance. Offering regular counselling could help schools spot the signs of abuse and neglect at home and give children a chance to speak up when potentially told not to by bullies or people at home. Mental health is a big deal, this could potentially save lives of children who need to be heard.",
        "background": "The Government should require all schools to offer regular counselling to all students, working together with social services and NHS mental health support teams, to give students a chance to speak up and be heard! ",
